text: Carrington is an unincorporated community in Callaway County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== Carrington was laid out in 1872 by William Carrington, and named for him. A post office called Carrington was established in 1873, and remained in operation until 1954. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Callaway County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Carrington, Missouri
